    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - TACHOMETER INPUT
        CIRCUITS - CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
        <para>The ECM (Electronic Control Module) provides the VPM (Vehicle Personality Module) with a 0 - 12 volt
            digital signal that indicates engine speed. The VPM buffers this signal and supplies the instrument panel
            with a signal to operate the tachometer. The frequency sent by the ECM is 1/5th of the actual engine RPM.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
